stringConverter - package stringConverter
This package contains all the stuff needed to convert a String to a Function
stringToFunction(String) - Static method in class stringConverter.FunctionBuilder
Uses FunctionBuilder.stringToFunction(String, String, String) to convert the input to a Function
It trys to find out the variable, and function name from the String, otherwise it will just use the following defaults:
functionName = "f" variableName = "x" These will be resolved from the following form:
"functionName(variableName) = ..."
stringToFunction(String, String, String) - Static method in class stringConverter.FunctionBuilder
Converts a String to a Function.
stringToReversePolishNotation(String, String) - Static method in class stringConverter.FunctionBuilder
Converts the functionTerm to Tokens and sorts them into the reverse polish notation.

sumUp() - Method in class functions.AdditionNexus
If this AdditionNexus contains other AdditionNexuses, this method moves all of their content into this AdditionNexus

For example:
AddVerknuepfung.funktionsTeile[AdditionNexus[Sin , PowerFunction], ExponentialFunction] toString: "(Sin + PowerFunction) + ExponentialFunction" results in: AddVerknuepfung.funktionsTeile[Sin, PowerFunction, ExponentialFunction] toString: "Sin + PowerFunction + ExponentialFunction"
sumUp() - Method in class functions.FactorNexus
If this FactorNexus contains other FactorNexuses, this method takes all FunctionParts contained by the other FactorNexuses and moves them into this FactorNexus

For Example: FaktorVerknuepfung.fucntionParts[FactorNexus[Sin , PowerFunction], ExponentialFunction] "(Sin * PowerFunction) * ExponentialFunction" results in: FaktorVerknuepfung.functionParts[Sin, PowerFunction, ExponentialFunction] "Sin * PowerFunction * ExponentialFunction"
sumUpFactors() - Method in class functions.FactorNexus
Multiplies the factors of all FunctionParts in FactorNexus.functionParts to one product.
